        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 3:12AM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 312 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Stoneville, or 34 miles southwest of Faith, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Red Owl, Marcus, and Stoneville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
